  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nTruffle Test will output redundant decodings for \"ambiguous\" events that aren't really so ambiguous.  Basically you'll have a bunch of different contracts that declare the same event, and Codec will be like, well, I know what this event is, but I don't know which contract declared it!  So it's ambiguous!  This creates a bunch of annoying redundant output.\r\n\r\nSo, we'll need to figure out how to handle this.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.1.67",
